	<a name="footnote24-26911_000_031">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.33-40?lang=eng#32" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 84:33&ndash;40</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.19?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">132:19</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/abr/2.11?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Abraham 2:11</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-26911_000_031">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/3.19,21?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Acts 3:19, 21</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote26-26911_000_031">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/27.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 27:13</a>. Paul also prophesied of our day &ldquo;that in the dispensation of the fulness of times [the Lord] might gather together in one all things in Christ, both which are in heaven, and which are on earth&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/1.10?lang=eng#9" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Ephesians 1:10</a>).</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote27-26911_000_031">27.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/27.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 27:6</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-26911_000_031">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p>It is appropriate that Moses, who first led God&rsquo;s children to the land of their inheritance, would be the one to commit the keys of the gathering of Israel to the restored Church. Moses had come to Peter, James, and John on the Mount of Transfiguration and there had bestowed upon them the same priesthood keys in their day. At the conference of the Church in April 1840, the Prophet Joseph Smith appointed Orson Hyde to go to Jerusalem and there dedicate the land for the return of the Jews and scattered Israel.<sup class="noteMarker">
	  <a href="#footnote44-26911_000_031">44</a>
	</sup> On Sunday, October 24, 1841, Elder Hyde knelt on the Mount of Olives and dedicated that land for the gathering of the Jews and of Israel to their ancient inheritance.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-26911_000_031">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/110.11-12?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 110:11&ndash;12</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-26911_000_031">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/110.14-15?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 110:14&ndash;15</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-26911_000_031">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Significant is the fact that Moses, Elias, and Elijah came on Easter Sunday, at the beginning of Passover.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-26911_000_031">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/mal/4.5-6?lang=eng#4" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Malachi 4:5&ndash;6</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-26911_000_031">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/110.16?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 110:16</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-26911_000_031">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/jacob/1.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Jacob 1:7</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.26?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Omni 1:26</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.30,32?lang=eng#29" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moroni 10:30, 32</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.59?lang=eng#58" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 20:59</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-26911_000_031">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/137.6-8?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 137:6&ndash;8</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote36-26911_000_031">36.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-cor/15.29?lang=eng#28" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Corinthians 15:29</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-pet/4.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Peter 4:6</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote37-26911_000_031">37.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/10.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matthew 10:6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/15.24?lang=eng#23" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">15:24</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote38-26911_000_031">38.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/jer/16.16?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Jeremiah 16:16</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote39-26911_000_031">39.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/20.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Nephi 20:13</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote40-26911_000_031">40.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/6.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 6:6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/11.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">11:6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/12.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">12:6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/14.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">14:6</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote41-26911_000_031">41.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Nephi 9:2</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote42-26911_000_031">42.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Bruce R. McConkie, in Conference Report, Mexico City Mexico Area Conference 1972, 45.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote43-26911_000_031">43.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/97.21?lang=eng#20" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 97:21</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-26911_000_031"><a name="-26911_000_031">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote44-26911_000_031">44.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Nephi 9:2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/10.7-9?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">10:7&ndash;9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/25.16-17,20?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">25:16&ndash;17, 20</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/21.22-28?lang=eng#21" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Nephi 21:22&ndash;28</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/29.7-8?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 29:7&ndash;8</a>.</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
                                        
